  "prompt": "What percentage of people using Quora have ever heard of \"Google\"?",
  "response": "It is reasonable to assume that the vast majority of people using Quora have heard of Google. Google is one of the most well-known and widely used companies in the world, and its search engine is a fundamental part of the internet experience for billions of users globally. Quora users are typically internet-savvy individuals who actively seek information online, so it is highly likely that nearly all of them are aware of Google.\n\nTo quantify this, it would not be unreasonable to estimate that **99% or more** of Quora users have heard of Google, given its ubiquitous presence in technology, search, and daily life. The remaining fraction might include very young children, individuals in extremely remote or low-tech environments, or those who are entirely new to the internet.",
